data.title: The Arkansas Democrat-Gazette - Arkansas' Best News Source
data.meta_description: Carpenter-Henning Ashley Elizabeth Henning became the bride of Michael Joseph Carpenter on June 1 in St. Theresa Catholic Church. The Rev. Mark Wood officiated.
data.text:
Carpenter-Henning

Ashley Elizabeth Henning became the bride of Michael Joseph Carpenter on June 1 in St. Theresa Catholic Church. The Rev. Mark Wood officiated.

The bride is the daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Michael Henning of Hensley. The groom is the son of Mr. and Mrs. Richard Carpenter of Conway.

Honor attendants were Brandi Stehle, Carly Hood and Seth Carpenter.

The couple will reside in Little Rock after a honeymoon in the Florida Keys.

Beauchamp-Graham

First United Methodist Church of Heber Springs was the setting Saturday for the marriage of Leah Kathryn Graham and Richard Bruce Beauchamp Jr.

The Rev. Tommy Toombs officiated.

Mr. and Mrs. Mike Graham of Heber Springs are the parents of the bride. The groom is the son of Mr. and Mrs. Rick Beauchamp of Fort Smith.

Katy Graham, Sydney Bridges, Anna Moon, Rein Beauchamp and Brian Beauchamp were honor attendants.

The couple will make their home in Fort Smith after their honeymoon.

Kane-Zimmerman

Chelsea Taylor Zimmerman became the bride of John Christian Kane on Saturday at Marsh Landing Country Club in Ponte Vedra Beach, Fla. The Rev. Sandra Hedrick officiated.

The bride is the daughter of Rhonda and Brian Zimmerman of Jacksonville, Fla. The groom is the son of Elaine and Steven Raby of Ponte Vedra Beach and Kathy and Mark Kane of Little Rock.

Honor attendants were Jessie Zimmerman Hedrick and Addison Kane.

After a honeymoon in Cancun, Mexico, the couple will make their home in Little Rock.

Ward-Boyce

Nuptial vows were exchanged by Lillian Jane Boyce and Michael Shawn Ward on June 1 at the home of the bride’s mother. The Rev. Stephen Davis officiated.

Parents of the bride are Mrs. Charles Clay Boyce of Russellville and the late Dr. Boyce. The groom is the son of Mr. and Mrs. Nolen Dewayne Ward of Booneville.

Mrs. Briant Noland, Mrs. Alan Tedford, Mrs. William McMillan and Dax Ward were honor attendants.

After a honeymoon in Curacao, the couple will make their home in Little Rock.

Bentley-Davidson

Wedding vows were exchanged by Hannah Elizabeth Davidson and Justin Marcus Bentley on Saturday in Park Hill Baptist Church. Ken Davenport officiated.

The bride is the daughter of Mr. and Mrs. James Davidson of North Little Rock. The groom is the son of Mr. and Mrs. Mark Bentley, also of North Little Rock.

Honor attendants were Amy Danza and Matt Cyrus.

The couple will reside in North Little Rock after a wedding trip to Saint Lucia.

Hoffpauir-Waters

Wedding vows were exchanged by Jana Diane Waters and Tyler Edward Hoffpauir on June 1 in Nettleton Baptist Church in Jonesboro. Chad Logan officiated.

Parents of the bride are Mr. and Mrs. John Waters of Jonesboro. The groom is the son of Mr. and Mrs. Kyle Hoffpauir of Wynne.

Jodi Waters, Nicole Lindsey and Grant Hoffpauir were honor attendants.

After a wedding trip to Ochos Rios, Jamaica, the couple will live in Jonesboro.

Holaway-Rogers

Stephanie Brooke Rogers and Brendan Ty Holaway were united in marriage Saturday at Old Mill Wedding Chapel in Hot Springs. Harold Nash officiated.

The bride is the daughter of Phyllis Whitcomb of North Little Rock and Phyllis and John Rogers of Sherwood. The groom is the son of Patti and George Holaway of North Little Rock.

Honor attendants were Paige Matlock, Jerryd Holaway and Neil Holaway.

After a wedding trip to Sandestin, Fla., the couple will reside in Jacksonville.

Sanders-Waller

Katie Teresa Waller and Zachary Scott Sanders exchanged marriage vows June 3 at the home of the groom’s grandparents, Mr. and Mrs. Gerald Russenberger of Wye.

Parents of the bride are Barbara Waller of Little Rock and the late Barry Waller. The groom is the son of Mr. and Mrs. Keith Sanders, also of Little Rock.

Alicia Colvin and Jim Stallings were honor attendants.

After a honeymoon in Ocho Rios, Jamaica, the couple will live in Conway.

Sanders-Voisin

Aimee Lauren Voisin became the bride of Landon Todd Sanders on May 18 on the steps of the Old State House.

Parents of the bride are Susan and Scott Vahle of Conway and Kathy and Calvin Voisin of Bayou Sorrell, La. The groom is the son of Joann and Todd Vint of Conway and Sarah and P.T. Sanders of Danville.

Honor attendants were Lily Strack and Preston Sanders.

The couple are living in Conway after a wedding trip to Germany.

Parsons-Baer

Kelsey Marie Baer became the bride of Cliff Ryan Parsons on Saturday in Pavilion in the Park. David Brown officiated.

Debbie and Mark Baer of Little Rock are the parents of the bride. The groom is the son of Trish and Nick Parsons of Conway.

Honor attendants were Karsen Baer and Drew Parsons.

After a honeymoon in Saint Lucia, the couple will make their home in Columbus, Ga.

O’Neal-Green

Nuptial vows were exchanged by Kellye Nicole Green and Ryan Andrew O’Neal on Saturday in First Assembly of God, North Little Rock. The Rev. Rod Loy officiated.

Parents of the bride are Connie and Michael Green of Hensley. The groom is the son of Judy and Ben O’Neal of Hot Springs.

Honor attendants were Brittney Kiefer and Eric O’Neal.

After a wedding trip to Orland, Fla., the couple will reside in Hot Springs Village.

Weatter-Signaigo

Allison Nicole Signaigo and Cory Rhoads Weatter were united in marriage Saturday in Immanuel Baptist Church.

The bride is the daughter of Cindy and John Signaigo of Little Rock.

Parents of the groom are Sue and Richard Weatter of Alexander.

The couple are honeymooning in Mexico.

Brett-Marks

Wedding vows were exchanged by Christine Marie Marks and William Tyler Brett on Saturday in Fayetteville Town Center, Fayetteville. Phillip Marks officiated.

Parents of the bride are Nancy Marks and Dr. Stephen Marks, both of Little Rock. The groom is the son of Allison Luchsinger of Cabot.

Laura Kahle and David Isom were honor attendants.

The couple will live in Fayetteville after a honeymoon in Playa Del Carmen, Mexico.

Brooks-Mendelsohn

Katheryn Elizabeth Mendelsohn became the bride of Parker Bryson Brooks on Saturday in Calvary Baptist Church. Bill Wellons officiated.

Parents of the bride are Sonya Marie and Dr. Lawerence Alan Mendelsohn of Little Rock. The groom is the son of Mary Clare and the late Stanford Finney and Stephen and Melissa Brooks, all of Dallas.

Mary Alexandra Mendelsohn, Jacquelyn Mendelsohn Hall and Stephen Harold Brooks II were honor attendants.

The couple will make their home in Dallas after a honeymoon in South Africa and The Republic of Seychelles.

Plattner-Frieberg

Diana Katherine Frieberg and Ross Benham Plattner were united in marriage May 14, on the beach in Gulf Shores, Ala. Ron Benham, uncle of groom, officiated.

Parents of the bride are Kathi and Brad Frieberg of Little Rock. The groom is the son of Sue Plattner Smith of Fort Smith and the late Greg Smith.

Meredith Frieberg, Seth Plattner, Brad Plattner and Adam Plattner were honor attendants.

The couple are living in Fayetteville and plan to take a wedding trip next summer.

Selby-Burrow

Lonoke Baptist Church was the setting Saturday for the marriage of Samantha Burrow and Jared Selby. The Rev. Steve Walter officiated.

The bride is the daughter of Nancy and Lester Burrow III of Lonoke. Parents of the groom are Lisa and Jeff Brewer of Sherwood and Ron Selby of North Little Rock.

The couple will honeymoon in the Caribbean.

Connor-Bright

St. Edward Catholic Church was the setting Saturday for the marriage of Megan Elizabeth Bright and John Michael Connor III. The Rev. Patrick Malone officiated.

Parents of the bride are Judy and Benny Bright of Maumelle. The groom is the son of Rosalind and John Connor Jr of Nashville, Tenn.

Honor attendants were Ashley Simmons and John Coulter.

After a honeymoon in the Pacific Northwest, the couple will live in Memphis.
